Lagos – Oba Jimoh Adewale-Cole, Oluojota of Ojota Kingdom, has implored the federal and state governments to look into the welfare of all categories of traditional rulers in the country. Oba Olawale-Cole,who spoke during a town hall meeting with the community chiefs and people, lamented that the welfare of some traditional rulers in the country was an eyesore. He emphasized the import of traditional rulers in the scheme of things in the country, stressing that as leaders at the grassroots, they are close to the people, and as such should be well taken care of. The monarch also urged Nigerians to embark on  prayers for the country,  saying, “We have to commit this country into the hands of God in order to save it from disintegration.” He identified corruption as the bane of the country, stressing that President Muhammadu Buhari had been doing his best to return sanity to the nation, even as he advised that in the war against graft, the government and the anti-graft agencies should be humane. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 